--- G/Physics Constraints
+++ D1/Physics Constraints
@@ -1 +1 @@
-Burgers residual with trainable viscosity: u_t + u*u_x - nu*u_xx = 0, retaining the nonlinear convection term u*u_x (dropping it linearizes the physics and invalidates the inference). Measurement data loss on the sparse noisy observations - without the observation data term the viscosity is not identifiable. Initial condition loss on u(x,0) = -sin(pi*x); boundary condition loss under the stated Dirichlet assumption. The viscosity must remain positive: use a positive parameterization nu = exp(theta) rather than an unconstrained scalar.
