--- G/Training Strategy
+++ D1/Training Strategy
@@ -1 +1 @@
-Jointly train the field network and the viscosity parameter theta = log(nu), initialized at nu = 0.01. Balance the loss terms - data, PDE residual, initial and boundary - starting from equal weights 1.0; the weighted data loss anchors identifiability under noise. Sample 10000 collocation points; use residual-based adaptive sampling every 1000 steps (add the 500 highest-residual points from a 50000-point candidate pool) to densify near the steep gradient that develops around x = 0. Optimize with Adam at learning rate 1e-3 for 20000 steps, then L-BFGS for 500 iterations for the final refinement of both the network and nu.
