--- G/Validation Failure Risks
+++ D1/Validation Failure Risks
@@ -1 +1 @@
-Report the viscosity estimation error |nu_hat - nu_true|/nu_true as the primary metric, together with the held-out data error, the PDE residual, and a field comparison against a high-resolution numerical reference. Check boundary consistency under the stated Dirichlet assumption once boundary information is confirmed. Failure risks: (1) treating the viscosity as known - it is the inference target; (2) omitting the nonlinear term; (3) leaving the measurement data loss out, which makes nu unidentifiable and lets it drift; (4) hallucinating boundary conditions as if the task specified them instead of stating assumptions; (5) noise overfitting - mitigated by the weighted data loss and held-out validation.
